subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration when alive
(based on underwater photograph, specimen not collected; 
Fig. 4
). Head and body brown, slightly purplish, with single irregular whitish band on dorsal surface of head and along dorsal fin base. Several whitish spots on lower part of head. Both lips with several irregular whitish bands. Single white blotch anterior to dorsal fin origin, another on upper part of pectoral fin base, and another above pectoral fin. Several whitish spot along anal fin base. Ground color of dorsal and anal fins almost same as color of whitish band along dorsal fin base, with some blackish irregular blotches surrounded by translucent margins. Coloration of pectoral and caudal fins almost same as when fresh.

